  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc6\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8  \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb2\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The problem is reducing power outage time",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Sri Lanka Electricity Board has reported that several power plants in the country are facing difficulties in operating due to shortage of furnace oil.",
        "Due to this, the power plant activities have decreased and the daily power cut has been forced to increase to three hours, the council also pointed out.",
        "The Electricity Board said that while 2,500 metric tons of furnace oil is required for the operation of power plants including Yugadanavi and Sabugaskanda, only 1,400 tons of oil is available.",
        "The Electricity Board has indicated that the activities of thermal power plants will be limited due to this.",
        "The council also said that the power capacity provided by hydro and coal-fired power plants is insufficient to meet the country's electricity needs.",
        "The Electricity Board of Sri Lanka also informed that since the Sapugaskanda Refinery operations have resumed, it is expected that the required furnace oil will be supplied to the power plants soon.",
        "This announcement came at a time when the power outage time was expected to be reduced as the faulty generator at Nuraicholai thermal power station was connected to the national power grid."
      ],
